race.comment: BRENLYN'S LEGACY (1) is a promising gelding on his way through. Was a strong winner last time over this track and trip to make it three on end. Has a strong association with Parish and should be hard to stop again, despite carrying the big weight. DANCEENUFF (3) knuckled down bravely to get the bob when resuming at Albury. Left it too late last time but closed strongly to just miss. Peaking now and is sure to be very competitive. LYRICAL BEAUTY (11) was firmly supported off a 403-day break and gave a bold sight but ultimately lacked fitness. May need another hitout but should give another sight. NARCISSIST (8) will bounce straight to the front from his inside alley and be in this for a long way.
